Description: Fragment of oval handle from neck join to sharp turn of Rhodian pottery a transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp with caduceus symbol.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '13.' Name Andrikos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0316.15.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (29)
